data.value: The node sets and edges sets do not need to be disjoint.
Composing preserves the attributes of nodes and edges. Attribute values from H take precedent over attribute values from G.
It is recommended that G and H be either both directed or both undirected.
For MultiGraphs, the edges are identified by incident nodes AND edge-key. This can cause surprises (i.e., edge
may or may not be the same in two graphs) if you use MultiGraph without keeping track of edge keys.
If combining the attributes of common nodes is not desired, consider union(), which raises an exception for name collisions.

children.type_: C: A new graph with the same type as G
